rd world view with no other bases for judgements bar imparted knowledge from specific inderviduals it does not create a role in which education can be child centred in that it becomes an enviroment of independent learning as all decisions on learning will be ascribbed to the processes of education the child has allready gone through which will be produced inderviduals who formulate the childs knowledge base. I'm not suggestting current state education is any better but i dont feel home education can be said to impart any less a dogmatic worldview ect. "/><type4:DocumentMetaData xmi:id="13" sofa="1" begin="0" end="865" language="en" documentId="974" isLastSegment="false"/><types:WebArgumentMetadata xmi:id="24" sofa="1" begin="0" end="0" author="cbarr" date="06 November 2009 11:01pm" docType="artcomment" origUrl="http://discussion.theguardian.com/comment-permalink/6750023" topic="homeschooling" thumbsUp="0" thumbsDown="0" origId="974" notes="" title="Ridiculous rules for home schools"/><type6:Paragraph xmi:id="39" sofa="1" begin="0" end="865"/><cas:View sofa="1" members="13 24 39"/></xmi:XMI>